timeline.bodyText:
Although, there is inherently nothing wrong with this code, the intent would be clearer if these tests have their own lines.
final Path appPath = Objects.requireNonNull(paths.getAppPath(), "Application path can't be null");
final String appName = Objects.requireNonNull(projectConfiguration.getAppName(), "Application name can't be null");
if (!Files.exists(appPath.resolve(appName))) {
    throw new IOException("Application not found at path " + appName);
}
Process runProcess = startAppProcess(appPath, appName);

or something like this:
Objects.requireNonNull(paths.getAppPath(), "Application path can't be null");
Objects.requireNonNull(projectConfiguration.getAppName(), "Application name can't be null");
final Path appPath = paths.getAppPath().resolve(projectConfiguration.getAppName());
if (!Files.exists(appPath)) {
     throw new IOException("Application not found at path " + appPath);
}

